arch:property.oc:show_val: Period of abandonment. The arch is reused as a squatter's camp--collapsed stucco and architectural elements reused as a temporary floor level. A cache of Late Roman coins (Locus 11) was found associated with these levels.

Phase X: Site abandonment post major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c, Upper level robbing occurs including the upper treads of East and West Interior and Rear Staircases, and the associated upper landings. Evidence of squatter camps in the South Corridor and Central Arch.
Locus 13 extends from the southeast corner of Locus 13 into the balk.

Locus 13, 7.5 YR 4/4 (Munsell Brown), and a concentration of dark clay, 5Y 4/2 (Olive Gray) is a uniform layer of debris spanning the trench. Locus 13 is a clayish dirt layer, more moist than Loci 6 or 10 but not as cakey as Locus 12.
